---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
---
<BaseLayout title="Install BridgeAIChat Control Host" description="Install and run the BridgeAIChat gateway and hosted UI.">
  <section class="surface">
    <div class="eyebrow">Install</div>
    <h1>Set up the control host.</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      The control host runs the gateway and serves the web UI. For the public macOS path, Homebrew is the intended
      install experience. The release archive remains the fallback for beta testers and manual validation.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section-gap grid two">
    <div class="card stack">
      <div class="eyebrow">Preferred</div>
      <h2>Install with Homebrew</h2>
      <pre>brew install bridge-ai-chat/tap/bridge-app
bridge-gateway</pre>
      <p>The formula installs a <code>bridge-gateway</code> launcher that serves the bundled UI directly.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card stack">
      <div class="eyebrow">Fallback</div>
      <h2>Use the release archive</h2>
      <pre>tar -xzf bridge-app_v0.1.0-beta.1_darwin_arm64.tar.gz
cd bridge-app_v0.1.0-beta.1_darwin_arm64
bash install-app.sh</pre>
      <p>The packaged installer copies the gateway and UI into <code>~/.bridge-app/current</code> and installs a local launcher.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-gap grid two">
    <div class="card">
      <div class="eyebrow">Verify</div>
      <h2>Check the gateway</h2>
      <pre>bridge-gateway

# open in a browser
http://localhost:8080</pre>
      <p>If the page loads but no devices appear, install an agent on another machine and point it at the gateway's Tailscale address.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <div class="eyebrow">Startup</div>
      <h2>Optional service mode</h2>
      <p>The packaged installer can register the gateway as a startup service through launchd on macOS or systemd on Linux.</p>
      <div class="note"><strong>Tip:</strong> service mode is best once you have already confirmed the UI works with a manual first launch.</div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
